Appeal Board
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:In NZ among the many administrative-judicial appellate tribunals known as appeal boards the ?two most widely known are perhaps: a. The Public Service, now State Services, Appeal Board, established mainly as a tribunal in which public servants may appeal against the State Services Commission's determinations, mainly non-promotion and salary gradings.  b. The Military Service Appeal Board(?s) to which conscripts appealed against call-up for  military service in ?WW1 and WW2, and after WW2 from 19-- to 19--, conscripted trainees could appeal against drafting into compulsory military training (CMT).
